[DQR.IFRS.0101.9536] The concept ifrs-full:OtherInflowsOutflowsOfCashClassifiedAsFinancingActivities appears in the investing cashflows of the companies cash flow statement. ifrs-full:OtherInflowsOutflowsOfCashClassifiedAsFinancingActivities is a financing item and it is expected that this item would only appear in the cash flow generated from financing activities. Please review the calculations defined for the cash flow statement to determine that the correct element has been used for this item.
Rule Element Id:9536 Rule version: 18.0.0RC1 -

[DQR.IFRS.0126.9595] The statement CashFlows includes an inconsistent calculation. The value of the concept ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInFinancingActivities of 412,348,000 should be equal to the sum of its child components defined in the calculation linkbase. The sum of these child components is 414,346,000. The values of the addends is determined by adding the values of the child concepts with a decimal value of -3. All values in the financial statements should use the same decimal value. The values reported in the financial statement in the current reporting period of 2020-04-01 to 2021-03-31 should be complete if the financial statement is to be mathematically accurate and complete. The components of ifrs-full:CashFlowsFromUsedInFinancingActivities that should add to 412,348,000 are comprised of the following:
+ CashFlowsFromUsedInFinancingActivitiesDiscontinuedOperations -2,000 - InterestPaidClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 2,066,000 - PaymentsFromChangesInOwnershipInterestsInSubsidiaries 2,000 (Incorrect decimals: 0 ) + ProceedsFromBorrowingsClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 321,058,000 + ProceedsFromCurrentBorrowings 143,166,000 + ProceedsFromIssuingShares 930,000 - RepaymentsOfBorrowingsClassifiedAsFinancingActivities 48,928,000 + FinancingReceivedFromReimbursedToMinorityShareholders 190,000
The addends are calculated based on the calculation linkbase defined for CashFlows. If addends are missing then the calculation tree should be amended. The rule will not add dimension components as the financial statement does not include a table. If dimensions are used on the statement then add a table to ensure that the dimensions are defined correctly.
